intro: Dalea elegans var. onobrychioides, commonly known as the slender milkvetch, is a flowering plant native to the western United States. It belongs to the legume family, Fabaceae, and is characterized by its slender, erect stems and small, pea-like flowers. The plant typically grows in dry, sandy soils and is adapted to arid environments. It has compound leaves with small, oval-shaped leaflets and produces pods that contain several seeds. This variety is often found in open habitats such as grasslands and rocky slopes.
